    "details": "URI nameConstraints from constrained intermediate CAs are parsed but not enforced during certificate chain verification in `wolfcrypt/src/asn.c`. A compromised or malicious sub-CA could issue leaf certificates with URI SAN entries that violate the nameConstraints of the issuing CA, and wolfSSL would accept them as valid.",
